cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on pedestrian detection, which falls under the sub-category of object detection. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes an active detector, which involves decision-making and policy-based approaches, indicating that it could also be categorized under cs.AI. The use of CNNs and the hierarchical feature representations also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (machine learning). The proposed approach involves coordinate transformation actions, which could be categorized under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could also suggest a potential categorization under multimedia (cs.MM).
